The Kano State Police Command on Friday said it has rescued a four-year-old boy, Abdulrahman Dalha who was kidnapped at Zangon Rimi quarters in Ungoggo Local Government Area of the state. The command’s Public Relations Officer, DSP Abdullahi Haruna, confirmed the development in a statement to NAN. He said, ‘A complaint was received on Nov. 10 at about 1500hrs at Zango Police Division that unknown persons had kidnapped one Abdulrahman Dalha, a four-year-old boy of Zango quarters, Ungoggo LGA of Kano State, demanding N4 million as ransom.” According to Haruna, the command’s Anti-kidnapping team of Operation Puff-Adder was immediately mobilised and directed to track down, arrest and bring the perpetrators to book within 24 hours. He stated that the operatives swung into action and arrested the principal suspect at Zangon Dakata quarters while planning to collect the ransom.
The Police spokesman said the principal suspect, Anas Isa, 22, confessed to the commission of the crime and led Puff-Adder operatives to the house of his aunty at Inusawa village in Ungoggo Local Government Area where the kidnapped victim was rescued. “His accomplice, Umar Hassan, popularly known as Liman of Zangon Rimi, a relative to the victim was apprehended. “The suspects will be charged to court as soon as investigation was concluded, “ he added. He, therefore, called on residents of the state to continue to cooperate with the police by giving timely information for prompt response. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.